DW, have we fixed the "Invalid stack frame" exception in another bug report?

The JDI exceptions don't share a common ancestor below RuntimeException, so we'll have to 
either add catch clauses for each exception that can occur (there should be quite a few), or we can 
do something clever like:
  catch (RuntimeException e) {
    if (!e.getClass().getName().startsWith("com.sun.jdi")) { //$NON-NLS-1$
      // Rethrow non-JDI exceptions
      throw e;
    }
    JDIDebugPlugin.log(e);
  }
